      <div resp="part:emfr" type="translation">
        <p n="1">
		Prosperity! Fortune!
	</p>
        <p n="1">
		[...]th year of Nṛpatuṅga.
	</p>
        <p n="1-2">
		<supplied reason="subaudible">I,</supplied> Pātirikiḻār Ciṅkaṉ of [...]puram, have given seven <foreign>mā</foreign>s of field [...]

	</p>
        <p n="2">
		We have become those who will present a glorious perpetual lamp, as long as the moon and the sun, <supplied reason="lost">to</supplied> [...].

	</p>
        <p n="2">
		We, the villagers, will protect this pious act.

	</p>
        <p n="2">
		This, if opposing/failing, […]<note>This lacunose sentence appears to state what happens in case of default.</note>

	</p>
